Social factors in frequent callers: a description of isolation, poverty and 
quality of life in those calling emergency medical services frequently.

Agarwal G(1), Lee J(2), McLeod B(3), Mahmuda S(4), Howard M(5), Cockrell K(6), 
Angeles R(7).

Author information:
(1)Department of Family Medicine, McMaster University, David Braley Health 
Sciences Centre, 100 Main Street West, 6th Floor, Hamilton, ON, L8P 1H6, Canada. 
gina.agarwal@gmail.com.
(2)McMaster University, 100 Main Street West, 6th Floor, Hamilton, ON, L8P 1H6, 
Canada.
(3)Hamilton Paramedic Services, Hamilton, Canada.
(4)SickKids Centre for Global Child Health, 100 Main Street West, 6th Floor, 
Hamilton, ON, L8P 1H6, Canada.
(5)Department of Family Medicine, McMaster University, 100 Main Street West, 6th 
Floor, Hamilton, ON, L8P 1H6, Canada.
(6)Western Sydney University, School of Science and Health, Hamilton, Canada.
